    <h2>About Our Shop</h2>
    <p>Penn Automotive is a full-service auto-body and collision repair facility established in 1959. Owner Joel Feldman is the only mechanical engineer in Pittsburgh to run his own collision shop — a licensed damage appraiser and mechanic with over 30 years of experience.</p>
    <p>We work on foreign and domestic vehicles and light trucks, and we use <strong>PPG automotive finishes exclusively</strong>, applied in a state-of-the-art paint booth with a proper curing process.</p>

    <h2>What's Included</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Free estimates (about 10 minutes)</li>
      <li>Lifetime written warranty on all repairs</li>
      <li>Work with all insurance companies</li>
      <li>Rental car pickup and return coordination</li>
      <li>Regular communication via phone or email throughout your repair</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The Repair Process</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Preliminary estimate</strong> — stop in for a free 10-minute walkthrough</li>
      <li><strong>Schedule your repair</strong> — we'll find a time that works for you</li>
      <li><strong>Parts confirmation</strong> — we confirm parts are on hand before you drop off</li>
      <li><strong>Drop off your vehicle</strong> — we handle everything from there</li>
      <li><strong>Updates throughout</strong> — we keep you informed by phone or email</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Common Questions</h2>

    <h3>Can I choose my own repair shop?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Pennsylvania law gives you the right to choose any repair facility you want, regardless of what your insurance company recommends.</p>

    <h3>What is a deductible?</h3>
    <p>Your deductible is the amount you pay out-of-pocket before insurance covers the rest. We can explain how it applies to your specific claim when you come in for an estimate.</p>

    <h3>Do you work with rental cars?</h3>
    <p>Yes. We coordinate rental car pickup and return through major providers so you're not left without transportation during your repair.</p>

    <h3>What does your warranty cover?</h3>
    <p>All repairs come with a lifetime written guarantee on workmanship. If something isn't right, we make it right.</p>

